1
00:00:04,758 --> 00:00:08,667
And as far as understanding the soul,
we read the Bhagavad-gītā,

2
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:11,127
the second chapter 
of the Bhagavad-gītā—

3
00:00:11,127 --> 00:00:15,557
many different things 
are mentioned there,

4
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:18,575
things in the Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam 
and elsewhere,

5
00:00:18,575 --> 00:00:21,405
so we get the impression 
or the understanding

6
00:00:21,405 --> 00:00:24,729
that there’s a cumulative effect

7
00:00:24,729 --> 00:00:30,159
of hearing about the nature, the qualities,
the characteristics of the soul,

8
00:00:30,159 --> 00:00:36,149
and that becoming a realized position.

9
00:00:38,624 --> 00:00:42,638
It’s not an intellectual exercise,

10
00:00:42,638 --> 00:00:49,724
although certain systematic representations 
have been given, such as:

11
00:00:49,724 --> 00:00:55,034
manasas tu parā buddhir
yo buddheḥ paratas tu saḥ

12
00:00:55,034 --> 00:00:59,784
indriyāṇi parāṇy āhur
indriyebhyaḥ paraṁ manaḥ 
[Bg: 3.42]

13
00:00:59,784 --> 00:01:04,764
This is one śloka from the Gītā saying,
“There are the objects of the senses;

14
00:01:04,764 --> 00:01:08,294
the senses are higher 
than the objects of the senses;

15
00:01:08,294 --> 00:01:13,564
higher than the senses is the mind,
which is the seat of sense experience;

16
00:01:13,564 --> 00:01:17,761
more refined than the mind 
is buddhi, or intelligence,

17
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:21,317
which is the discriminating factor
that the mind lacks;

18
00:01:21,317 --> 00:01:24,006
finer than that is the soul plane.

19
00:01:24,006 --> 00:01:28,499
So it’s giving us a systematic way
in which we can understand—

20
00:01:28,499 --> 00:01:32,529
it’s something fine and subtle.

21
00:01:32,529 --> 00:01:34,649
And another śloka says,

22
00:01:34,649 --> 00:01:37,649
āścarya-vat paśyati kaścid enam
[Bg: 2.29]

23
00:01:37,649 --> 00:01:41,891
If you have a glimpse of that plane,
you’ll be astonished.

24
00:01:41,982 --> 00:01:45,428
So we can understand:
having a glimpse of the soul plane,

25
00:01:45,428 --> 00:01:50,581
a glimpse of our identity,
some sense,

26
00:01:50,581 --> 00:01:58,209
a glimpse of its reality, its prospect—
we’ll be astonished.

27
00:01:58,209 --> 00:02:01,279
So we can understand 
from our present position

28
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:07,350
that that glimpse
may be like lightening;

29
00:02:07,797 --> 00:02:11,615
like we’re seeing here
in the last few days

30
00:02:11,615 --> 00:02:13,801
as the rainy season 
is approaching:

31
00:02:13,801 --> 00:02:17,193
when there is lightening,
more in the evening,

32
00:02:17,193 --> 00:02:21,623
momentarily everything
becomes illuminated.

33
00:02:22,023 --> 00:02:26,596
So from our present position
at different moments

34
00:02:26,596 --> 00:02:37,256
we may have some glimpse
of ātmā, of our spiritual self,

35
00:02:37,256 --> 00:02:43,444
but there’s no magic wand
or trick to turn that ‘on’,

36
00:02:43,444 --> 00:02:47,272
to leave it in the ‘on’ position.

37
00:02:47,272 --> 00:02:52,286
It will be by cumulative effect 
of hearing ...

38
00:02:52,286 --> 00:02:54,706
Śravaṇaṁ, kīrtanam, smaraṇam etc.—

39
00:02:54,706 --> 00:02:59,458
hearing, chanting, remembering, serving—
a variety of things.

40
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:03,341
At different times 
we’ll be put in situations

41
00:03:03,341 --> 00:03:10,861
where out of necessity 
we’ll have to go deeper.

42
00:03:10,861 --> 00:03:15,467
So, we can understand 
at least theoretically

43
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:18,597
that we are conscious 
living beings.

44
00:03:18,597 --> 00:03:22,815
But we can also add to that
that we are covered by layers

45
00:03:22,815 --> 00:03:26,442
of acquired prejudice

46
00:03:26,442 --> 00:03:29,772
from being, from living 
in conditional existence.

47
00:03:29,772 --> 00:03:33,872
For how long?
Since times immemorial.

48
00:03:34,466 --> 00:03:40,243
So in that position 
of acquired prejudice,

49
00:03:40,243 --> 00:03:44,993
layers of false ego,

50
00:03:45,383 --> 00:03:50,876
how will we come in contact 
with the self?

51
00:03:50,876 --> 00:03:53,216
But what we said before, 
referring to …

52
00:03:53,216 --> 00:03:58,322
Gurudev gave a famous talk called
“Demolishing the pillars of ego.”

53
00:03:58,322 --> 00:04:07,553
So what is it that will dissolve
the false concept of self

54
00:04:07,553 --> 00:04:12,811
and promote 
the proper concept of self?

55
00:04:12,811 --> 00:04:15,981
That will be spiritual association.

56
00:04:16,571 --> 00:04:20,546
‘sādhu-saṅga’, ‘sādhu-saṅga’—
sarva-śāstre kaya

57
00:04:20,546 --> 00:04:25,006
lava-mātra sādhu-saṅge 
sarva-siddhi haya 
[Cc: Madhya, 22.54]

58
00:04:25,006 --> 00:04:28,919
He told, “Through spiritual association
our position will improve.

59
00:04:28,919 --> 00:04:32,827
By getting superior association.”

60
00:04:33,807 --> 00:04:38,307
So it’s gradual and cumulative.

